ANN vs CNN
===========


| Feature                  | ANN (Artificial Neural Network) | CNN (Convolutional Neural Network)     |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------------- | -------------------------------------- |
| Full Form                | Artificial Neural Network       | Convolutional Neural Network           |
| Mainly Used For          | Structured data, tabular data   | Images, videos, visual data            |
| Input Handling           | Treats all pixels independently | Preserves image spatial structure      |
| Feature Extraction       | Manual or limited               | Automatic feature extraction           |
| Layers Used              | Fully connected layers          | Convolution, Pooling, Fully Connected  |
| Image Processing Ability | Weak                            | Very strong                            |
| Parameters               | Large number of parameters      | Fewer parameters due to filter sharing |
| Training Speed           | Slower for images               | Faster and more efficient for images   |
| Accuracy on Images       | Lower                           | Higher                                 |
| Overfitting              | More chances                    | Less chances compared to ANN           |
| Best Example             | House price prediction          | Face recognition, digit classification |
| Real-World Usage         | Banking, sales prediction       | Self-driving cars, medical imaging     |


============

Simple Understanding
--------------------

ANN
Every neuron connects to every neuron.
Does not understand image patterns properly.

Works better for:
numerical data
prediction tasks
classification on structured datasets

-----------------------

CNN
Specially designed for images.
Detects:
edges
curves
textures
objects

====================

Uses filters and pooling to learn image features automatically.

Why CNN is Better for Images

Example:
A cat image.

ANN:
Sees only pixel numbers.

Cannot understand nearby relationships effectively.

CNN:
Detects ears, eyes, edges, shapes.
Learns patterns step-by-step.

That is why CNN gives much better accuracy in image recognition tasks.
===================================

Architecture Difference
-----------------------

ANN Flow

Input → Hidden Layer → Hidden Layer → Output

CNN Flow

Input → Convolution → ReLU → Pooling → Flatten → Fully Connected → Output

=============================

Accuracy Difference (Typical)
-----------------------------

| Model | Image Classification Accuracy |
| ----- | ----------------------------- |
| ANN   | 20% – 70%                     |
| CNN   | 90% – 99%                     |


depends on dataset and training quality)

